The paper discusses the architecture and resource provisioning methods in federated cloud, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). It also talks about the benefits of federated cloud in terms of cost minimization, performance maximization, and collaboration, which could be categorized under Computer Communications (cs.CC) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The paper also mentions the challenges associated with efficient resource provisioning, which could be classified under Software Engineering (cs.SE) and Systems and Control (cs.SY).
